  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MuTA96">
<l>vāḻttiya vāyarāy vāṉōr maṇimakuṭan</l>
<l>tāḻtti vaṇaṅkat taḻumpāmē – kēḻtta</l>
<l>vaṭittā maraimalarmēṉ maṅkai maṇāḷa</l>
<l>ṉaṭittā maraiyā malar</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Because the celestials, as those whose mouths praise [him], lower</l>
<l>[their] jewelled crowns [and] bow [to them], they are scarred,</l>
<l>– the blossoms that are the lotus feet<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">Here I suggest we understand aṭi tāmarai as tāmarai aṭi, reversed for the sake of etukai.</note> of the husband</l>
<l>of the girl on the lotus blossom with a lustrous stalk.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
